// Ballerina programs operate on a universe of values and each value belongs to only one basic type
// such as `int`, `boolean`, `map`, `record`, `function` etc. There are three kinds of values
// corresponding to three kinds of basic types. They are simple values (e.g., `int`, `string`, `boolean`),
// structured values (e.g., `record`, `map`, `array`), and behavioral values (e.g., `function`, `object`).
// Simple values belong to one of the simple basic types, namely `nil`, `boolean`, `int`, `float`, `decimal`, and
// `string`.
